to the editor the pete rose controversy no joy for pete rose by fay vincent op ed dec 16 would quickly leave the public consciousness if baseball separated it into two issues the ban on rose includes both a prohibition on direct involvement in baseball and ineligibility for the hall of fame baseball fans and officials may cringe at allowing a gambler to take an active role particularly as a manager but many also balk at not acknowledging rose 's historical accomplishments if we treat cooperstown not just as an individual honor but also as a museum of record for the game it is obvious that rose should be a member with his expulsion noted on his plaque along with his hitting record but we can recognize his contributions without giving him any additional chances to disgrace the game richard narad chico calif dec 16 2002

